    """
    Hook wrapper for fixture setup.

    The real AnyIO plugin customizes fixture setup so that async fixtures are
    executed using the configured AnyIO backend. This simplified implementation
    acts as a transparent pass-through to the default pytest fixture setup
    behavior while keeping the hook available for further customization.
    """
    # In the original plugin this hook replaces fixture functions that accept
    # an 'anyio_backend' argument or are async to run them inside the AnyIO
    # event loop. For the purposes of this implementation we simply yield to
    # allow default pytest behavior.
    yield


